CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 26, 1961, pg. A2, reads: "Like Mama? - Sculptor William Anderson's 'Glory of Expression' presents a real 'puzzlement' to these two fledgling art lovers, William and Gordon Sladge. The brothers were among the many Pittsburghers who offered moral support to local artists, during the recent exhibit at Ammon Center. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Women, men, and boys viewing artwork hung on chain link fence at outdoor art exhibition, Ammon Center
